{"title":"Eddy Merckx Bikes Are Back… and Yes, in Steel!","link":"https://theradavist.com/eddy-merckx-steel-bikes-2024/","date":1705505513000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1366\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?fit=1200,1366&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxMolteni.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>We received news this morning that <a href=\"https://www.eddymerckx.com/\">Eddy Merckx</a> has re-launched the brand, including steel and titanium bikes amongst the flashy carbon fiber racing machines…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1366\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?fit=1200,1366&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxGreen.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>This <a href=\"https://www.eddymerckx.com/en_US/bikes/platform/Pevele\" target=\"_blank\">Molteni Pévèle</a> (48 mm tire clearance – €2,149.00 for a 2x Tiagra build) is an homage to Eddy’s three times winning Paris-Roubaix, embodying what a modern steel bike would have looked like back in the early 1970s. Steel is not only more budget-friendly than carbon; it is durable, stiff, and yet comfortable. Perfect for an all-road bike.</p>\n<p>The classic steel frame is an ode to the glorious past of Eddy Merckx bicycles. The team bikes from 7 Eleven, Telekom, Motorola and last but not least the classic Merckx – Molteni bike, these bikes left an indelible impression on many bicycle enthusiasts. But make no mistake, these are not retro bikes, they are steel bicycles with a subtle nod to the past.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"6387\" height=\"4258\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?fit=1200,4258&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?w=6387&amp;quality=75 6387w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/EddyMerckxCorsa2024.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>There is also the Corsa model, available in Titanium. Each frame is <a href=\"https://www.eddymerckx.com/en_US/pages/corsa\" target=\"_blank\">welded by hand in Belgium</a>.</p>\n<p>Check out more details at <a href=\"https://www.eddymerckx.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Eddy Merckx</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/eddy-merckx-steel-bikes-2024/\">Eddy Merckx Bikes Are Back… and Yes, in Steel!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"208f4b13d95f7fc3545ee352d8e6956e2e5af42e272739e48f0820f8e5c92b9b","category":"Cycling"}